To Clone Git Reposatoray in System use
⦁	git clone "Repository Link" 

mohit@First-Hokage MINGW64 ~
$ git clone https://github.com/Mohit-Bairwa25/Learning-Git-GitHub.git


cd is for change of directoray in terminal
⦁	cd "Folder Name"


⦁	ls is used for list of files
PS D:\HDD Data\A Disk\CODE\Visual Studio Code\GiT Demo\Learning-Git-GitHub> ls

    Directory: D:\HDD Data\A Disk\CODE\Visual Studio Code\GiT Demo\Learning-Git-GitHub

Mode                 LastWriteTime         Length Name
----                 -------------         ------ ----
-a---          12-05-2024 01:42 PM              2 Clone & Status
-a---          12-05-2024 01:42 PM            807 Configuring Git
-a---          12-05-2024 01:42 PM           1488 Setting Up Git, GitHub & GitBash.md 


To View Hidden Files Type
⦁	ls -a
This is used to view All Files


To Know The Status of Your File Type
⦁	git status
PS D:\HDD Data\A Disk\CODE\Visual Studio Code\GiT Demo\Learning-Git-GitHub> git status   
On branch main
Your branch is up to date with 'origin/main'.

nothing to commit, working tree clean


After a Change in Your File Save Your File with Ctrl+s
and Check status again it wil show
PS D:\HDD Data\A Disk\CODE\Visual Studio Code\GiT Demo\Learning-Git-GitHub> git status 
On branch main
Your branch is up to date with 'origin/main'.

Changes not staged for commit:
  (use "git add <file>..." to update what will be committed)
  (use "git restore <file>..." to discard changes in working directory)     
        modified:   Clone & Status

no changes added to commit (use "git add" and/or "git commit -a")


Affter adding a new file it will show that file as a untracked file
PS D:\HDD Data\A Disk\CODE\Visual Studio Code\GiT Demo\Learning-Git-GitHub> git status
On branch main
Your branch is up to date with 'origin/main'.

Changes not staged for commit:
  (use "git add <file>..." to update what will be committed)
  (use "git restore <file>..." to discard changes in working directory)
        modified:   Clone & Status
        modified:   Configuring Git
        modified:   Setting Up Git, GitHub & GitBash.md

Untracked files:
  (use "git add <file>..." to include in what will be committed)
        Add & Commit

no changes added to commit (use "git add" and/or "git commit -a")



There are 4 Types of Status
1.untracked
new files that git doesn"t yet track


2.modified
changed


3.Staged
files is ready to be commited


4.unmodified
unchanged